#: ../../../guide-plugin-language.md:263
msgid ""
"Create `rust-core/src/prose/tinylang.rs`. This module receives the parsed"
" tree-sitter AST and returns a `Vec<ProseRange>` -- the byte ranges of "
"prose text plus any exclusion zones within those ranges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide-plugin-language.md:267
msgid "The structure has three parts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide-plugin-language.md:269
msgid ""
"**1. Configuration constants** -- lists of node kinds and command names "
"that control what gets skipped:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide-plugin-language.md:288
msgid ""
"**2. AST walk** -- a recursive function that collects `text` leaf node "
"byte ranges, skipping non-prose subtrees:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide-plugin-language.md:336
msgid ""
"**3. Range merging** -- adjacent text nodes are merged into sentence-"
"level chunks. Gaps between text nodes are analyzed: if a gap contains "
"only whitespace and punctuation (after stripping language-specific noise "
"like math and commands), the ranges merge. If a gap contains a paragraph "
"break (`\\n\\n`), a new `ProseRange` starts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide-plugin-language.md:342
msgid ""
"Math regions within bridgeable gaps are recorded as exclusion zones so "
"the grammar checker sees spaces instead of math content:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide-plugin-language.md:381
msgid ""
"The `is_bridgeable_gap` and `collect_math_exclusions` helper functions "
"are language-specific. See `rust-core/src/prose/tinylang.rs` for the full"
" implementation, including `strip_tinylang_noise` which removes math, "
"commands, code spans, bold/italic markers, and comments from a gap before"
" testing whether it is bridgeable."
msgstr ""

